{\par \b Syntax:}\par exbisector(Point1, Point2, Point3)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Given three points that define a triangle, creates the bisector of the exterior angles of the triangle whose common vertex is at the first point. The triangle does not have to be drawn in the Plot view.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par exbisector(GA, GB, GC) draws the bisector of the exterior angles of \u916?ABC whose common vertex is at point A.\par \par exbisector(0,\u8211?4i,4) draws the line given by y=x\par }